            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Wilkes barre Pa.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>Aug. 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1849</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">At a meeting of the Jewish<lb/> Congregation on the
                    <date>11th</date> inst: the following<lb/>
                <sic>Resulations</sic> was <sic>unanimusly</sic> adapted.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">1d That the Congregation, will for ever Remember<lb/> the
                    <sic>kindniss</sic> and charitable feelings, of the <persName>Rev:<lb/> Mr.
                    Leeser</persName> towards the Congregation.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> That it would afford us unfeigned
                pleasure<lb/> to have you here; on the day we <sic>consicrate</sic><lb/> our new
                    <sic>Synagoge</sic>, which will be on the <date>31st</date> inst:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> That we remitt our thanks to you, with the<lb/>
                <sic>asurance</sic> that your benevolence will never be<lb/>
                <sic>vergotten</sic> in the <sic>heards</sic> of the Congregation<lb/> {Bene
                Berriss) in <placeName>Wilkesbarre</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">4d That a copy of this meeting be <sic>forward</sic> to<lb/> you,
                and to be Published in some of your City Papers</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Respectfully, <persName role="author">M. N. Strouse</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Coresp: Sectry.</p>
            <p>To.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Rev: Mr. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Phild.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>P.S. The <persName>Rev: Mr. Isaacs</persName> of<lb/>
                <placeName>New York</placeName>, will be here also,<lb/> on the day we
                    <sic>Consicrate</sic> our new <sic>Synagoge</sic></p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You will please forward by Rayt<add>?</add>,<lb/> one Prayer Book
                according to the German<lb/> &amp; Polish custom with English translation<lb/> also
                2 Hebrew Alphabets.</p>
            <p>Should you have some <sic>dayly</sic> Prayer Books like<lb/> the above, and willing
                to send me some on<lb/>
                <sic>Comision</sic> I be able to sell more, for you,<lb/> as regard
                    <sic>refferance</sic>, please inquire of my<lb/> name, at <persName>Mr.
                    Weils</persName>. corner of <placeName>Race &amp; Second Sts</placeName>:</p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Phild.</placeName>
                <hi rend="indent(1)">
                    <persName role="author">M. N. Strouse</persName>
                </hi>
            </p>
            <p>P.S.<lb/> The payment for the above<lb/> shall be <sic>remittit</sic> as soon as
                I<lb/> know the price.</p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Rev: Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>118. South fourth Str</placeName>:</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName>.</p>
